    "body": "I suspect we use `abortable-iterator` too much. The way we handle timeout is straightforward but we have to base on AbortController to throw Error for pipe, and in my case I can only see timeout error if I press `Ctrl + C`. Having a look at `abortable-iterator`, I found quite complex code there with `while(true)` and it has to handle multiple abort signals..\r\n\r\nSince our case is quite simple, I'd like to handle aborting async iterator ourself instead of keeping `abortable-iterator` busy ... ",
